The Yangtze River main stream to achieve full coverage of the water green integrated service area - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Wuhan, December 11 (Xinhua Wang Xian) Fuling water green integrated service area in Chongqing City was completed and put into operation on schedule on the 10th, which is the second water green integrated service area officially operating in the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, following the listing of the 8th Luzhou water green integrated service area in Sichuan Province. So far, the water green integrated service area has covered the upper, middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River. Qiu Jianhua, deputy director of the Yangtze River Shipping Administration of the Ministry of Transport, said that previously, Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, Jiangsu and other provinces have built and operated 10 water green integrated service areas in the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River, which have been recognized by the majority of the crew and played an important role in promoting the high-quality development of Yangtze River shipping. The full coverage of the green integrated service area on the water is another milestone event in the construction of green shipping on the Yangtze River, and the pollutant receiving and shipping service capacity of Yangtze River vessels has been significantly improved. According to the introduction, the water green comprehensive service area is an important facility for the majority of ships, crew members to provide a full range of production, life services, to help the majority of crew members to solve the "urgent difficulties and worries" problem. The two green integrated service areas on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, integrated with life services, production services and government services, with green environmental protection as the theme, ship repair and ship emergency rescue services as the characteristics, to achieve the port ship "a berthing, multiple services", will make the crew of the Yangtze River more efficient work, more convenient life. It will make the work and life of crew members sailing in Yangtze River more efficient and convenient.
